This paper deals with the problem of differentially private histogram release, which is a common problem in the field of privacy-preserving data analysis. The paper focuses on two different partitioning strategies for releasing histograms, which are commonly used in database systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also deals with privacy and security issues, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves formal analysis and quantification of errors, which is related to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the implementation and evaluation of algorithms, which is related to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves the use of information theory, which is related to the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory).
